        "subject": "LU-19504 contrib: script to resolve strings in objdump",
        "message": "LU-19504 contrib: script to resolve strings in objdump\n\ncan be useful to understand disassembled code:\n\n# objdump-resolve-str.sh mdd.ko\n...\n0000000000000b50 <mdd_recovery_complete+0x120> mov $0x0,%rdi\n    b53: R_X86_64_32S .data+0x1840\n0000000000000b57 <mdd_recovery_complete+0x127> mov $0x0,%rdx\n    b5a: R_X86_64_32S  .rodata.str1.1+0x6c  # mdd != ((void *)0)\n0000000000000b5e <mdd_recovery_complete+0x12e> mov $0x0,%rsi\n    b61: R_X86_64_32S  .rodata.str1.1+0x13  # ASSERTION( %s ) failed:\n0000000000000b65 <mdd_recovery_complete+0x135> movl $0x40000,0x0(%rip)\n    b67: R_X86_64_PC32 .data+0x1850\n0000000000000b6f <mdd_recovery_complete+0x13f> call 0000000000000b74\n    b70: R_X86_64_PLT32 libcfs_debug_msg-0x4\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <bzzz@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I55f5ef77a704970fe67d2cc663d8049e1cd0237d\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61928\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Artem Blagodarenko <ablagodarenko@ddn.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
